text.tspan: Carbon intensity vs. GDP per capita, 2021
Carbon intensity represents the quantity of CO₂ emitted per unit of energy consumption – it's measured in kilograms
of CO₂ emitted per kilowatt-hour of energy.
Source: Global Carbon Budget (2022); U.S. Energy Information Administration (EIA); Energy Institute Statistical Review of World Energy (2023),
Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
Note: GDP per capita is measured in constant international-$ which corrects for inflation and cross-country price differences.
